				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-611345#post-1761418</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-611345/scp-1296#post-1761418</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 27 Apr 2013 13:54:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Voct</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>392303</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>For a black-and-white llama: &quot;sure thing. Any particular coat pattern? You want stripes? Spots?&quot;</p> <p>For a fat-free llama: &quot;uh, look, pal, this is an animal. Animals have fat on their bodies, it's the way animal bodies work. We can get you a <em>skinny</em> llama, a <em>malnourished</em> llama, but it'll have fat in its body <em>somewhere</em>. Even brains are fatty, you know?&quot;</p> <p>For a decaf llama: &quot;You know llamas don't actually <em>have</em> caffeine, right?&quot;</p> <p>For a geek llama: &quot;&#8230; yeah, sure, it's a geek llama. Loves that <em>Throne Games</em> stuff. Can't get enough of the Magical cards. Really.&quot;</p> <p>For a Mary-Sue llama: &quot;Sure, you can name the llama anything you want. We don't got any just now that answer to that name, but they learn pretty quick.&quot;</p> <p>For a Bright llama: &quot;Honestly, pal, there ain't <em>that</em> much variation in their intelligence. I mean, if you had a bunch of brain-damaged llamas, then sure, a normal llama would be brighter than the others, but&#8230; oh. D'you mean, like, with headlights? 'Cause I <em>guess</em> we could hook up some headlights to one, maybe some flares, but &#8212; what? The fuck are you talking about? Nine six three what?&quot;</p> <p>For a cracked llama: &quot;cracked like fractured? Okay. Any particular bones? Skull, jaw, front legs, back legs, ribs, what? Oh, and you want they should be old breaks or new? Old breaks, like they're already healed but you can tell they were there when you examine the bones, you know? Or fresh breaks that still need to heal? I mean, yeah, we've got some pre-damaged ones available, but we can also do some custom damage if you want. Plus there's the teeth, we could just crack the teeth.&quot;</p> <p>For a cool llama: &quot;Gonna let you in on a secret, pal: <em>all</em> llamas are cool! In fact, they're <em>super</em> cool!&quot;</p> <p>For a lock-picker llama: &quot;well, uh. Some llamas can&#8230; open gates, maybe? Like, with latches? They can open a latch if it's a big enough latch&#8230; I think? Like&#8230; to their paddock? I mean&#8230; look, they don't have <em>hands</em>, okay? Llamas don't have hands. Unless you mean, like, putting a bunch of locks in front of a llama, and getting it to choose one of them, like it's PICKING the lock! See, it's funny 'cause the word 'pick' has two meanings.&quot;</p> <p>For a Lolita llama: &quot;Um. You're&#8230; do you want to <em>fuck</em> the llama? Is that what you're asking for? I mean, it's not any of my business, really, but&#8230; no, I'm not saying we <em>can't</em> sell it to you, I just wanna make sure we get the order right.&quot;</p> <p>For all the other requests: &quot;&#8230;. goddamn idiot kids making their goddamn stupid prank calls. <strong>*&gt;CLICK&lt;</strong>*&quot;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
